      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That sounds good, but I need to be very precise for the legal documentation. When you say \"completely anonymized,\" are we talking about true anonymization under GDPR standards—where the data can never be linked back to an individual—or are we using pseudonymization where certain identifiers are just replaced by keys? I need to know if there is any technical pathway, however difficult, to cross-reference this with other datasets to re-identify a user.",
